@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Squarado" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed.

                             How to play?

  To play, click on any tile, the bar displayed on it will rotate
clockwise by 45 degres. To complicate matters a little, you cannot
click two or more times consecutively on the same bar, as it will
rotate only once; you have to click on another bar before clicking
again on the same bar.

  To create an alignment, 3 bars or more have to be lined-up and
the orientation of the bars must be the same as their alignment.
In other words: for an horizontal alignment, the bars must be
horizontal.

  When an alignment of bars has been made, those bars will be
removed from the board and you will get points according to the
number of bars that were lined-up; 1 point for 3 bars, 10 points
for 4 bars and 100 points for 5 bars.

  As you complete the first board, scoring gets higher on the
second board and up: when you make alignments of 4 bars or more,
the number of points you get is increased according to the number
of game boards that are completed. On board #2 4 bars will give
you 11 points and 5 bars will give 111 points; on board #3, 4 bars
give 12 points and 5 bars give 122 points, and so on...

  Another thing to watch for is that from the second game board;
from time to time, a bar will randomly be removed from that
board... If you are not careful, that could cause the game to end
pretty fast...

  Continue the game until the board is emptied, in which case,
Squarado will display a new board. If no alignments of at least
3 bars can be made, the game will be over.

  Squarado keeps the best score made since the game was run.

  Have fun!

  To quit the game, click on the game window's closebutton or by
pressing on the 'Esc' key.
    
